# Tool-only asset generation; no hardcoded segment / fixture references

## Three categories

A. **Cursor edits OK** (code, tests, wrappers, rules, top-level docs):
- `src/docgen/**`
- `tests/**`
- `docs/demos/_*.sh`
- `.cursor/rules/**`
- `AGENTS.md`, root `README.md`, `docs/demo-function.md`, `docs/yaml-generate.md`, `docs/session-notes*.md`
- `milestones/**`

B. **Hand-authored INPUTS / fixtures** (Cursor edits OK; **never** deleted by `clean-bundle` / reset; **not** LLM outputs):
- `docs/demos/hints/**` — **maintainer hint files** (`.md`, …). Use YAML **front matter** (`docgen.segment`, `docgen.wiring`) so **`docgen yaml-generate`** merges segment list, `visual_map`, and per-segment narration/manim paths into `docgen.yaml`. Do **not** hand-edit those merged keys in `docgen.yaml` in Cursor; edit hints and re-run **`yaml-generate`**. Hints also steer **`docgen narration-generate`**, **`docgen scene-spec-generate`**, etc. **They are not OpenAI outputs.** Other demo bundles may use the same `<bundle>/hints/**` convention.
- `docs/demos/terminal/*.tape` — VHS sources
- `docs/demos/scripts/*.py` — Playwright capture drivers (matched to segments by id-in-filename)
- `fixtures/**` — Playwright/Vite/etc. test apps; presence and project-type detected generically. The raw `*.spec.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,mjs}` files inside are the **input** to `docgen per-function-generate`.
- `docs/demos/narration/README.md`

C. **LLM/tool OUTPUTS — Cursor MUST NOT edit; only `docgen` (CLI/library) + OpenAI may produce:**
- `docs/demos/docgen.yaml` (owner: `docgen yaml-generate`)
- `docs/demos/narration/*.md` excluding `README.md` (owner: `docgen narration-generate`)
- `docs/demos/animations/scenes.py`, `docs/demos/animations/timing.json` (owner: **`docgen scene-compile`**, **`docgen scene-spec-generate`**, pipeline)
- `docs/demos/animations/specs/*.scene.yaml` — declarative Manim scene specs (owner: **`docgen scene-spec-generate`** with optional hand curation; compiled into `scenes.py` via **`docgen scene-compile`**)
- `docs/demos/audio/*.mp3` (owner: `docgen tts`)
- `docs/demos/per-function/*.docgen.yaml` and sibling `*.html` (owner: `docgen per-function-generate` — generated from raw Playwright specs in `fixtures/**`; wiped + regenerated each reset)
- `docs/demos/recordings/**` including `recordings/per-function/<slug>/*` and top-level aliases (owner: `docgen generate-all` and `docgen demo-function` driven by `_rebuild-per-function.sh`)

If a generator can't produce shippable output yet, **fix the generator** under `src/docgen/**`. Never paste/edit a category-C file to bridge the gap.

## No hardcoded segments or fixtures

`docgen` itself contains **no** hardcoded segment numbers, scene class names, tape filenames, or fixture paths. Discovery only:

- Segments → from `narration/<NN>-*.md` filenames.
- VHS → from `terminal/<segment_stem>.tape` presence.
- Playwright capture → from `scripts/*.py` whose filename contains the segment id.
- Manim → from `class …Scene` definitions in `animations/scenes.py`, in source order.
- Playwright projects (for `discover_tests.roots`) → from any directory with `@playwright/test` / `playwright` in `package.json` or a `playwright.config.{js,ts,mjs,cjs}`.

Tests are exempt: concrete ids and class names there are intentional test data.
